3ï¸âƒ£ Name based virtual hosting 
ğŸ‘‰ Name-based virtual hosts support routing HTTP traffic to multiple host names at the same IP address.
ğŸ‘‰ An ingress can route traffic to two different services for example1.com and example2.com using an ingress.

4ï¸âƒ£ TLS
ğŸ‘‰ TLS ingress is used to secure an ingress using the certificates for the hosts.
ğŸ‘‰  The Ingress resource only supports a single TLS port 443.
ğŸ‘‰  TLS termination happens at the ingress point and traffic to the Service ( and its Pods) will be in plaintext.

